  description="Understanding the key differences between an autism meltdown and a tantrum helps parents respond more effectively and with more compassion — for their child and themselves."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
    <nav class="text-sm text-stone-400 mb-8">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-stone-600">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <a href="/autism-meltdowns" class="hover:text-stone-600">Autism Meltdowns</a>
      <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <span class="text-stone-600">Meltdown vs Tantrum</span>
    </nav>
    <h1 class="text-display font-bold text-stone-900 mb-6">Meltdown vs Tantrum: What's the Difference?</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-10">
      They can look similar from the outside — but the cause, the response, and the support needed are completely different.
